headline: Fast food is a staple of American culture, but some of its workers struggle to survive
summary: FRESNO, Texas — The only moment TiAnna Yeldell has to herself is when she’s sleeping, and that doesn’t happen much. The 44-year-old single mom of three works 80-hour weeks to provide for her...
